# ‚ö†Ô∏è Important Issues You Must Fix

## üö® 1. LinkedIn Cookie Placeholder

You still have:

```json
"<COPY_YOUR_LINKEDIN_COOKIES_HERE>"
```

This will FAIL until you paste:

* Your `li_at` cookie
* Full cookie string

‚ö†Ô∏è Also be careful:
LinkedIn can block your account if scraping aggressively.

---

## üö® 2. LinkedIn Scraping Is Risky

This part:

```js
"value": "{{ $json.linkedin_cookies.match(/li_at=([^;]+)/)[1] }}"
```

If cookie format changes ‚Üí workflow crashes.

Better approach:

* Store `li_at` only
* Avoid regex extraction
* Save it as clean variable

---

## üö® 3. WhatsApp Number Is Hardcoded

```json
"recipientPhoneNumber": "44123456789"
```

You should:

* Make this dynamic
* Or store your real number

---

## üö® 4. Using Same Workflow as Subworkflow

You are using:

```json
"workflowId": "={{ $workflow.id }}"
```

This means:
It calls itself as subworkflow.

‚ö†Ô∏è That can cause recursion issues.

Better:

* Duplicate workflow
* Make a separate "Attendee Research Subworkflow"

---

# üí° How To Make This Production-Ready

### ‚úÖ 1. Add Error Logging

Add:

* Error trigger
* Slack/Email alert if scraping fails

---

### ‚úÖ 2. Add Memory (CRM Integration)

Instead of scraping LinkedIn every time:

Store:

* Attendee data in Notion / Airtable
* Only refresh monthly

Will reduce:

* API cost
* Scraping risk

---

### ‚úÖ 3. Upgrade LLM Model

Instead of:

```
gpt-4o-2024-08-06
```

Use:

```
gpt-4.1-mini
```

Cheaper + faster for summarization.

---

